sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG), where a total volume of 37,166 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.7 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 45.5% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 8.2 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $76.50 strike call option expiring June 15, 2018 , with 6,293 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 629,300 underlying shares of PG.

That number of contracts represents approximately 1.1 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 45.1% of SPWR's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.5 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $7 strike put option expiring June 15, 2018 , with 1,685 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 168,500 underlying shares of SPWR.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $270 strike call option expiring June 15, 2018 , with 695 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 69,500 underlying shares of DPZ.
